Environment: 2/5
Value of money spend: 2/5
Food: 1/5
Drink: 2/5

Once enter to the cafe the vibes given is not bad but after you been seated, the smoke and smell from cooking is overwhelming because it is an open kitchen here.

Visit here because some online reviewer said that this cafe is really worth to spend a meal here, but the truth is the overall experience is not that good I can said it is below average.

Me and my gf ordered a soba and luncheon rice. We both are feel so disappointed because my soba is obviously overcooked and the seasoning wasn’t tasty. Compared to my soba, luncheon rice is relatively better but still below average.

The fruit come along with the set is tiny, the fruit provided when I visit was watermelon. I can said any other cafe’s fruit 1 slice is bigger than my two slices.

The selling price wasn’t that cheap as what the reviewer mentioned. Two sets + 2 cups of fruit tea cost around RM60.

Would recommend the cafe to install another better smoke absorber or zone out the kitchen area. Review back your own menu and seasoning. For coffee, they are using liberica coffee beans, if you personally don't enjoy liberica, please don't come.

Price wise, it's quite reasonable, we spent like RM50 for 2 pax (2 meals, 2 drinks).

Overall, it was a less pleasant experience. I don't think I will be back.

My suggestion is instead prepare everything upon order, you can prepare them in the morning before you start your business.
